The paper deals with machine learning models for learning fair representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses image datasets and discusses visualizing changes, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions fairness definitions and protected characteristics, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the problem of unavailability of fair data, which could be related to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
